				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You DID notice that the treatment didn't cure the infection... only reduced the viral load?  That makes me nervous.  Viruses are incredibly resilient.  They mutate easily.  Any treatment that doesn't wipe out 100% of a viral infection just accelerates the mutational characteristics of the virus, and eventually produces a resistant strain.
