			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Relbeek...
<br />

<br />
Don't make me slap you.
<br />

<br />
This is the same sort of unfounded crazy-talk going around on the Art Bell show regarding Stem Cell research...
<br />

<br />
"Ooooh!  I could make the blind see and the crippled walk if only we vote for John Kerry!  Here's Christopher Reeves' bloody shirt in a reliquary!  Make a pilgrimage to Aventis-Pasteur to see it!"
<br />

<br />
The report is pretty clear about what the treatment is and does, and even making the VERY generous assumption that the clinical trials pan out, the economics of this are going to be terrifying.  This could fail for the same reason Flu Vaccines are unavailable:  nobody can earn a profit making it.
<br />

<br />
Yes, it's a promising new technique.  Yes it should be researched further and developed.  But it's NOT a cure-all.  Please take a deep breath and lower your expectations to a reasonably optimistic level.
<br />

<br />
Yeah, Stem Cells could theoretically repair spinal cord injuries.  And yeah, this could theoretically be an AIDS cure.  And maybe one day they will be.  But that day is not "around the corner".  And this could be the next "cold fusion" too.  We all remember how THAT one turned out.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
