			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Embar...
<br />

<br />
I'm waiting to see what happens when this treatment is combined with the normal spectrum of antiviral drugs currently in use against HIV.
<br />

<br />
Enabling the immune system to mop up the viral particles more effectively combined with drugs that basically slow the virus' replication may well enable the body to win a "war of attrition", at least in some of the least-advanced cases.  Maybe force the disease into remission like chemotherapy does to cancer.  Maybe even cure it.  And probably with similar success rates and similar side effects to chemotherapy.
<br />

<br />
It's hard to say, and the only way to know for sure is to do the work.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
